<h2 id="Map">The Map</h2>
<p>
    Territories give requisition points.
    Requisition points can be spent on upgrades.
    Each territory has a fixed terrain layout. This is known as the Operational Theatre Map.
    Deployment zones and strategic/operational advantage are determined as normal.
</p>
<p>
    By default a territory gives +10 RP per turn.
    A capital territory gives +30 RP per turn.
    A player starts with one capital territory and two normal territories, thus has 50 RP to spend in his first turn.
</p>
<h2 id="CampaignTurn">Campaign Turn</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Receive RP.</li>
    <li>Declare attacks.</li>
    <li>Resolve conflicts.</li>
    <li>Spend RP on territory upgrades.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="Territories">Territories</h2>
<h3 id="TerritoryUpgrades">Territory upgrades</h3>
All territory upgrades must be represented by appropriate scenery and/or tokens. Each upgrade may be placed only once per territory. Unless noted otherwise, the upgrade must be marked on the map and must always start the game in the exact same location.
